name: prDM
SDN:P01::prefLabel: Pressure (spatial coordinate) exerted by the water body by profiling pressure sensor and correction to read zero at sea level
definition: The force per unit area exerted by the water column on a mobile sensor located in the water column.

name: sigma-t00
SDN:P01::prefLabel: Sigma-T of the water body by computation from salinity and temperature using UNESCO algorithm
definition: Computed by UNESCO SVAN function using in-situ temperature

name: sigma-t11
SDN:P01::prefLabel: Sigma-T of the water body by computation from salinity and temperature using UNESCO algorithm
definition: Computed by UNESCO SVAN function using in-situ temperature

name: T090C_SDEV
SDN:P01::prefLabel: Temperature (ITS-90) standard deviation of the water body
definition: The square root of the average of the squares of deviations about the mean of a set of values of the specified measurement.

name: T190C_SDEV
SDN:P01::prefLabel: Temperature (ITS-90) standard deviation of the water body by second sensor
definition: The square root of the average of the squares of deviations about the mean of a set of values of the specified measurement.

definition: Unavailable

definition: Unavailable

name: Par
SDN:P01::prefLabel: Downwelling vector irradiance as energy of electromagnetic radiation (PAR wavelengths) in the water body by cosine-collector radiometer
definition: Unavailable

name: Sal00
SDN:P01::prefLabel: Practical salinity of the water body by CTD and computation using UNESCO 1983 algorithm
definition: This is the preferred term for this definition. Alternative term PSALST02 is included to cover cases where there are two sensors of the same type contributing to the data set and referential integrity considerations prevent a usage of a single code.

name: Sal11
SDN:P01::prefLabel: Practical salinity of the water body by CTD (second sensor) and computation using UNESCO 1983 algorithm
definition: This is the alternative term for this definition. Only use to cover cases where there are two sensors of the same type contributing to the data set and referential integrity considerations prevent a usage of a single code.

name: SvCM
SDN:P01::prefLabel: Sound velocity in the water body by computation from salinity and temperature using UNESCO algorithm
definition: The rate at which sound travels through the water column computed from salinity and temperature using UNESCO algorithm

name: Sbeox0V
SDN:P01::prefLabel: Raw signal (voltage) of instrument output by oxygen sensor
definition: The raw output from a dissolved oxygen sensor such as an SBE43 with output as a voltage related to DO concentration.

name: wetCDOM
SDN:P01::prefLabel: Concentration of coloured dissolved organic matter {CDOM Gelbstoff} per unit volume of the water body [dissolved plus reactive particulate phase] by in-situ WET Labs FDOM ECO fluorometer
definition: Quantity or mass of the specified analyte in a unit volume of an unfiltered sample of fresh or salt water.

name: FlSPuv0
SDN:P01::prefLabel: Fluorescence of the water body by linear-response CDOM fluorometer
definition: This code is under review due to its ambiguity. It is likely to be deprecated at the end of the review period. Please use terms stating 'Concentration of%' for calibrated CDOM fluorometer output or 'Raw signal% of%' for the raw fluorescence signal [updated 30/07/2019]. Definition was: The amount of violet to low ultra-violet radiation generated in the water column in response to high ultra-violet radiation transmission expressed relative to an unspecified baseline using fluorometer designed to detect CDOM
